
            Video
            In full: Nicola Sturgeon interview with Laura Kuenssberg on Brexit
            SNP leader Nicola Sturgeon says she wants to form a "coalition of opposition" to Theresa May's Brexit plans with Labour and other parties, ahead of a vote of MPs at Westminster.Scotland's First Minister tells the BBC's Political Editor Laura Kuenssberg she has held "exploratory" talks with Jeremy Corbyn and, in a separate meeting, with other opposition party leaders.She says she wants to ensure that a no-deal Brexit is not the only alternative to the PM's plans.
                
                        20 Nov 2018
                    
                
        
